courses.subject: Math
courses.customDesc:
Choose one of the following: MATH118, MATH119, MATH141, MATH161, or MATH221.

Required in Major or Support; also satisfies GE.

MATH116 and MATH117 may be substituted for MATH118.

courses.subject: GE
courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, C1, C2, Lower-Division C Elective, Upper-Division C, D1, D2, Lower-Division E, F, and GE Elective. Upper-Division C should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). Teaching candidates are advised to take KINE250 (E). One (1) course must be completed from B1, in addition to MATH118. Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR) requirements.
